4) Q1. Hans Rosling’s quiz

For each of the six pairs of countries below, which country do you think had the highest child mortality rates in 2015? Which pairs do you think are most similar?

gapminder %>%
  filter(year == '2015' & country %in% c('Poland', 'South Korea')) %>%
  select(country, infant_mortality)

5) Q2.

In order to analyze this world view, our first plot is a scatterplot of life expectancy versus fertility rates (average number of children per woman). We start by looking at data from about 50 years ago, when perhaps this view was first cemented in our minds.

- 1962년 대륙별 출산률과 기대수명
gapminder %>%
  filter(year == '1962') %>%
    ggplot(aes(fertility, life_expectancy, color = continent)) +
    geom_point()

- 1962년, 2012년 대륙별 출산률과 기대수명 비교
gapminder %>%
  filter(year %in% c(1962, 2012)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(fertility, life_expectancy, color = continent)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_grid(continent~year)

facet_grid는 Plotly library에서 facet_row = continent, facet_col = year의 argument를 담당한다.

- 1962년, 2012년 대륙별 출산률과 기대수명 비교
gapminder %>%
  filter(year %in% c(1962, 2012)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(fertility, life_expectancy, color = continent)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_grid(.~year)

.은 facet_grid의 row argument를 생략한다.

- facet_wrap

복수 년도와 특정 조건에 따른 faceting

years <- c(1962, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2012)
continents <- c("Europe", "Asia")
gapminder %>%
  filter(year %in% years & continent %in% continents) %>%
  ggplot(aes(fertility, life_expectancy, color = continent)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~year)

- facet_wrap with fixed scale
gapminder %>% 
  filter(year %in% c(1962, 2012)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(fertility, life_expectancy, color = continent)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(.~year, scales = "free")

Mode : Line

Mode : Multiple-Line
countries <- c("South Korea", "Germany")
labels <- data.frame(country = countries, x = c(1975, 1965), y = c(60, 72))

gapminder %>%
  filter(country %in% countries & !is.na(fertility)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(year, life_expectancy, color = country)) +
  geom_line() + 
  geom_text(data = labels, aes(x, y, label = country), size = 2) + 
  theme(legend.position = "none")

Q4. Purpose1 : If poor countirs have become poorer and rich countries become richer.

gapminder <- gapminder %>%
  mutate(dollars_per_day = gdp/population/365)

If dollars_per_day < 2 = absolute poverty

1970 GDP
past_year <- 1970 

gapminder %>% 
  filter(year == past_year & !is.na(gdp)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black")

1970, 2010 GDP
years <- c(1970, 2010)

gapminder %>%
  filter(year %in% years & !is.na(gdp)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black") + 
  facet_grid(.~year)

About log transformation

We need to choose correct log2() or log10() in situation.

years <- c(1970, 2010)

gapminder %>%
  filter(year %in% years & !is.na(gdp)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(log2(dollars_per_day))) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black") + 
  facet_grid(.~year)

Reordering
gapminder %>%
  filter(year == past_year & !is.na(gdp)) %>%
  mutate(region = reorder(region, dollars_per_day, FUN = median)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day, region)) +
    geom_point() +
    scale_x_continuous(trans = "log2")

Comparing multiple distribution with boxplot
gapminder <- gapminder %>%
  mutate(group = case_when(
    region %in% c("Western Europe", "Northern Europe", "Southern Europe", "Northern America", "Australia and New Zealand") ~ "West",
    region %in% c("Eastern Asia", "South-Eastern Asia") ~ "East Asia",
    region %in% c("Caribbean", "Central America", "South America") ~ "Latin America",
    continent == "Africa" & region != "Northern Africa" ~ "Sub-Saharan",
    TRUE ~ "Others"))

gapminder <- gapminder %>%
  mutate(group = factor(group, levels = c("Others", "Latin America", "East Asia", "Sub-Saharan", "West")))

원하는 순서가 있을경우 factor로 지정한다.

years <- c(1970, 2010)

gapminder %>% 
  filter(year %in% years & !is.na(gdp)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(group, dollars_per_day)) +
  geom_boxplot() + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) + 
  scale_y_continuous("log2") + 
  facet_wrap(~year) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

library(ggridges)
## Warning: package 'ggridges' was built under R version 4.0.5
gapminder %>%
  filter(year %in% years & !is.na(dollars_per_day)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day, group)) + 
  scale_x_continuous(trans = "log2") + 
  geom_density_ridges() + 
  facet_wrap(~year)

5. Final Code

past_year <- 1970
present_year <- 2010
years <- c(past_year, present_year)
gapminder %>%
filter(year %in% years & !is.na(gdp)) %>%
mutate(west = ifelse(group == "West", "West", "Developing")) %>%  ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day)) +
geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black") +
scale_x_continuous(trans = "log2") +
facet_grid(year ~ west)

country_list_1 <- gapminder %>%
filter(year == past_year & !is.na(dollars_per_day)) %>%
pull(country)
country_list_2 <- gapminder %>%
filter(year == present_year & !is.na(dollars_per_day)) %>%
pull(country)
country_list <- intersect(country_list_1, country_list_2)

past_year <- 1970
present_year <- 2010
years <- c(past_year, present_year)
gapminder %>%
filter(year %in% years & !is.na(gdp) &
country %in% country_list) %>%
mutate(west = ifelse(group == "West", "West", "Developing")) %>%  ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day)) +
geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black") +
scale_x_continuous(trans = "log2") +
facet_grid(year ~ west)

gapminder %>%
filter(year %in% years & country %in% country_list) %>%
ggplot(aes(group, dollars_per_day)) +
geom_boxplot() +
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +
scale_y_continuous(trans = "log2") +
xlab("") +
facet_grid(. ~ year)

gapminder %>%
filter(year %in% years & country %in% country_list) %>%
mutate(year = factor(year)) %>%
ggplot(aes(group, dollars_per_day, fill = year)) +
geom_boxplot() +
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +
scale_y_continuous(trans = "log2") +
xlab("")
